Benefits of the transferability of the catch shares include: 

• Reduced number of vessels and fishing capacity. 

» In the first year after the implementation of the Pollock Cooperative, only 16 
out of the 20 vessels fished; only 6 out of 10 fished in the Pacific Whiting fish-
ery post-implementation of the cooperative.22 

» New Zealand fisheries have seen a reduction in quota owners on the order of 
35  percent  since  the  program’s  inception  in  1986.  As  of  2003,  the  majority  of 
the reductions were in mid-size firms.23 

» The  Mid-Atlantic  Surf  Clam  and  Ocean  Quahog  fishery  has  seen  over  a  54 
• Greater  flexibility  provided  for  participants  to  match  quota  holdings  with 

percent decline in the number of vessels.24 

