Mr. BUNDY. Oh, could they? 
Senator CANTWELL. Yes, could they. 
Mr. BUNDY. Yes. They could if the Council put it on their agenda. 
And that is a big ‘‘if,’’ by the way, because there is a lot of competi-
tion to get on that agenda, and more proposals do not make it than 
do  make  it.  And  if  it  got  on  the  agenda,  then  it  would  be  some 
