not  affect  any  of  the  vessels  that  seem  to  be  the  focus  of  a  lot  of 
the  discussion  today,  the  H&G  trawl  fleet  and  the  H&G  longline 
fleet. If this legislation is going to do what it really probably ought 
to do, it needs to be much broader than it is right now. 

The  last  issue  is  that  that  language,  while  it  focuses  on  vessel 
replacement,  it  actually  has  another  very  important  component 
which is what we call an inshore permit stacking or quota stacking 
proposal. Again, this proposal makes a lot of sense. You have more 
catcher  vessels  inshore  than  you  need.  This  would  allow  vessel 
owners to take their quota off one vessel and put it on another ves-
sel, giving you the opportunity to make sure you have the most ef-
ficient  vessels  on  the  ground.  It  all  makes  great  sense  and  we 
ought to do it, but we ought to do it as a package. 

